==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stenoderm
<hw>Sten"o*derm</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>steno`s</grk> narrow, little + <ets>-derm</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any species of bat belonging to the genus
<gen>Stenoderma</gen>, native of the West Indies and South America.
These bats have a short or rudimentary tail and a peculiarly shaped nose
membrane.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stenodermine</ent>⟦br⟧
